casebody.data:
May 16, 1949.

Per Curiam Decisions.

No. 670. Securities & Exchange Commission v. Philadelphia Company. Solicitor General Perlman and Roger S. Foster for petitioner. Thomas J. Munsch, Jr. for respondent.

On petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the District, of Columbia Circuit.

Per Curiam:

The petition for writ of certiorari is granted. The judgment of the Court of Appeals is vacated and the case is remanded to that court with directions to dismiss the petition for review as moot, on joint motion for the parties.
